Quite possibly the worst chipotle location ever. 90% of the workers can't wrap a burrito to save their life and it's resulted in several hefty losses of filling. News flash: a burrito should not be folded like a piece of paper and the aluminum should COVER it.

Honestly the only reason I give any stars at all is for the happy blonde guy that's always there. I have yet to ask his name but youd know exactly who it is if you saw him. He's got this everlasting happy attitude and he creates an entire experience in the one-minute encounter you have with him
A+ human being and always a pleasure to be served by him!<//review>

< review>
I really really like the food. The chicken is fried well and very crisp! However it's not as good as it used to be. It used to be one of my favorite places but now the portions are noticeably smaller. The flavor is still awesome but you only get a few pieces of chicken now. The boba is ok here. < UserId.>
112828455244746111861</UserId.>
<username>Alizen< /username>< date>
1547370529781< /date>
<Rating>1</Rating>< Review>
One star for their misleading menu and overall service. I came here to try it out because for $10 their combo said it would come with a dipping sauce, choice of fries, and a boba drink.

Their combos include popcorn chicken with sweet potato fries, crispy chicken strips with sweet potato fries, jumbo chicken wings with regular fries, and a chicken rice bowl with a salad and rice.

The (presumably) owner of the store was very unhelpful. I said that the combo menu was very misleading and that there were 4 combos and that I was supposed to get fries, sauce, and a drink with it. He said if I wanted the fries then I could get the popcorn chicken combo. I told him that his menu does not state that. It says if I pick a combo I would get the sauce, fries, and drink. Clearly we were not speaking the same language so I just dropped it and didn't bother pushing it further.

The boba itself is a very large 30 oz beverage that comes with boba already. I opted for the taro smoothie which was well blended with the powder and boba that wasn't incredibly fresh but you could tell it was made that morning.

The chicken bowl was relatively lackluster. It was made inside the kitchen so you couldn't tell if it was made fresh or if it was just reheated. The chicken was popcorn chicken which I suppose was their specialty and it came with the driest salad in the world. They couldn't even bother with giving a dressing for it...

Overall, I would not come back here for a second visit based on my interaction with the employee and for the low quality taste of the food I had.<//Review>

<Name>Robin Morrison< /Name><Time>1536216933178<//Time><Rate>5< /Rate><gmap_id>0x80dcd82656cccf09:0x580dd41c2c8b006e<//gmap_id>< Text>
Loved the food and drinks here! Our group ordered the popcorn chicken with fries and chicken tenders with fries combo, both with original spice and the rice bowl with spicy spice and it was absolutely delicious! The chicken was perfectly cooked with the perfect amount of crunch and tenderness and the spices were a perfect compliment to them. Dipping them in the spicy sauce and ginger soy sauce made them even more delicious! The food was enough to share between 5 people and the drinks were massive! OMG they were huge! They were part of the combo so we got the Thai tea with boba for the combo and cookies and cream smoothie and enjoyed every last ounce of them.

I'm not from this area so throughout the whole meal, I kept telling my husband that I'm going to be craving this place so it sucks that we'll have to drive the hour and a half from San Diego to get it, LOL! If you're ever at the outlets, make sure to stop by here to try the food or at least to pick up their massive drinks :)<//Text>

< Text>
Great Breakfast and Drinks.
This place was recommended for breakfast and mimosas. The decor is very contemporary and clean. Service was friendly, prompt and constant.

The breakfast options aren‚Äôt very extensive but they make up For it with the quality.
The short stack of pancakes was very large and enough to feed two.
The Huevos rancheros were also large and came with a generous portion of avocado. Black beans are a rare find.

My wife‚Äôs BLAT sandwich was juicy, delicious and very well made. The fries were perfectly made: golden brown and delicious.
The Mimosas and bellinis were well made and tasty.

Fresh fruit drink garnish is a nice treat. Oh, and the pumpernickel bread option is a nice surprise. You don‚Äôt see that all the time.
Highly recommend this place.<//Text>

< Review>
Food: Breakfast tacos and garden scramble were both delicious. However, the coffee was mediocre and the orange juice was pretty bland.

Service: Friendly staff and timely food.

Atmosphere: They got rid of the heat lamps in favor of a tarp. Detracts from the ambience and covid safety, but I understand it is less costly. Location is next to a large road so it can get a little noisy.

Value: Food is a little pricey but generally worth it. The $5 bland orange juice is definitely way overpriced though.

Overall: I‚Äôll definitely come back here for the food. Great breakfast spot with just a couple shortcomings.</Review>

Did an order for footlong classic Italian BMT over the app. It was a great experience! The app interface needs to be adjusted a bit, but I was able to order pretty much what I wanted.

I ordered it for my home and drove about a mile, and it was waiting for me when I got there! They literally just handed it to me and I walked out the door! The process was so simple and so easy...

<Text>I ordered a dress from David's Bridal online. When I received it, it was too big. I scheduled an appt for alterations (bring it in at the bust, and shorten the length) and they quoted me $200. Mind you, this dress is a pretty plain, strapless bridesmaid dress with nothing fancy to it. I only paid $97 for the dress and somehow it is more to remove material than was to make the dress. Hmm. < review>
Last year in July 2017, I had scheduled an appt & arrived 15 minutes early.(when you walk in there is a door chimes) so I waited at the front desk, until 10 minutes AFTER my appt time had started (25 min total) I walked into the back & the worker there rudely asked, how did I get in there. I said I walked in the front door almost a half hour ago & have been waiting to check in. The attendant said, oh you don't have to check in. I said, I didn't know because I had an appointment. She laughed & said, No, I don't think you do... are you sure it was here? I said, yes, I am sure. Then I showed her my confirmation & she said, I should have your name on my appointments list. Then she walks away, grabs a clipboard & shows me the list & I show her my name RIGHT THERE ON THE APPOINTMENTS LIST.
REGARDLESS, I wasn't going to let THAT ruin my experience. So I told the worker that I was looking for something that made me look skinny-curvy but classy. I was currently 7 months pregnant & if I could find a dress design that would make me look pretty at THAT time, I would know THAT was the dress I would want to get married in after I had the baby. The lady looked at me & said well I don't know what kind that would be. Do you have any ideas? (I was shocked. Not even a suggestion. Maybe my hopes were up too high because of the show SAY YES TO THE DRESS, but this lady was making me feel like a FAT GIRL in a SKINNY PEOPLE ONLY store.) So I took out my phone & showed a few dresses of some dress designs online. The worker said, ya, we don't have anything like those. I said, I was just showing the dress shape I was looking at mostly. She said, you're welcome to look around & find something. I said, you're not going to grab me some dresses? She said, yes, sure what kinds?... I think you should wear an A-frame dress that design most women want to wear to get that shape you're looking for. I said, I don't want A-frame or ball gown because my fiance said he doesn't want anything too poofy where it would be hard to stand near me. So she said, ok, I will be back. You guys can go ahead & look while I do also. So we did. The attendant came back 5 min later with ALL A-FRAME or ball gown dresses!! I politely said, that's not what I wanted, I was looking for something more fit & flare something that hugs the body on the top a little bit doesn't really poof out at the bottom. She asked, are you going to even try any of these on? I said no, like I said, my fiance said he didn't want it to be poofy, so I don't even want to try them on, thank you. So she said she would be back with more dresses.
(Mind you, not one other customer was in the store except my wedding party)
After about 15 minutes of her gone (looking for dresses & passing by us with empty arms) & me trying 3 dresses we found ourselves, I was walking out in dresses & judging the right fit. The attendant came back, like she was putting inventory away. And Seen a couple of dresses that I asked get to pull in my size. She looked at them & said are you sure, this isn't going to give you the fit you're looking for, I mean, Iheard you say you looked too fat in the other dress & I'm just saying, this one isn't going to be more flattering. I said, it's fine. I like these, so can Ijust try them, I know I might not like it on, but Iwould like to at least try. She brought them back & basically stopped helping us from then on. We were alone, trying to figure out the front & back or which stap goes where. I began to feel defeated. I was trying on dresses for over an hour, apparently the lady who worked there was having a bad day & took it out on me.
The dresses were beautiful but not worth the experience, if it looks like I'm about to cry in some of the pictures it's because I probably was in some of them. Dress shopping should make you feel happy, it should make you want to come back. Not here</review>

< review>
I made an appointment, and had a very terrible experience. So bad that I left and placed the order for my bridesmaid dress online.

I was there at 10:30 AM, and I was the only one in the store. 2 employees were working - my "designer," and the lady that stands in front. My designer was a lady that helped me pick the dresses to try (I could get any style just had to be the correct color), but told me my size wasn't avail in all styles so she said she'd "clip the bigger sizes." I got dresses from 2-6, which is actually quite a large range.

The dresses here are firstly, so gross. They have sweat and deodorant stains, and are stretched from years of ppl trying them on. This I guess just comes with the territory, but gross. Most of the eye hooks are broken, so you can't even get a feel for the neckline/delicate piece that has the hook. You just have to hold it together with your hands and try to picture yourself in that dress with it hooked, so ghetto. The lady was never around to help so yes, I literally had to hold the neckline together with my hands and try to look at myself.

Upon trying them on for my appointment, I actually just ended up trying it all on alone. I'd put one on, walk around the store looking for the stylist, who was NEVER AROUND. Then she'd find me looking, offer some feedback and once I went back in the fitting room she'd say "I'll be right back," but she was NEVER RIGHT BACK! I zipped all 10 dresses on myself, did a spin and told myself what looked good and what didn't. What was the point of making an appointment to get help? She literally wasted so much time in my day, as I just kept waiting like an idiot. The lady in front was actually more helpful because I knew where to find her to ask for advice.

All in all, the lady supposed to be helping me never "clipped the dresses to make them fit," never helped zip the tight ones with tall zippers, or really assisted in my experience. I had the most terrible time, and it put me in the worst mood that I couldn't even smile or enjoy the experience. I wish I had never made an appointment and wasted 1.5 hours trying dresses on alone in an empty store. I can't even imagine how bad the service would be if there were more brides/bridesmaids.

I ordered online, and customer support on the phone was nice so I 100% recommend that and not going in the store. I will never return here.</review>

I have had two appointments with two stylists, and both Cherae and Rebeka were absolutely wonderful, and helped me with the impossible! They both were excellent at their jobs, didn't make me feel rushed, and made the experience feel intimate with their personal touch.

I am incredibly insecure with my body, and very indecisive, so I knew finding the right dress would be difficult.

I felt so overwhelmed going into my first appointment, but Cherae was so warm and welcoming, and put me at ease and made me feel completely comfortable.

She was very patient as I tried on all different styles of dresses, and made sure I was aware of all of the options available for each dress I tried on. She was beyond diligent and really passionate about her work, and that really made my experience!

For my second visit, I was styled by Rebeka, who provided every bit as much diligence and warmth, and really helped me make my final decision.

In addition to the quality of service -I- recieved, I really appreciated how kind and receptive she was to the quirky requests of my friend who wanted to try on a couple dresses, and feel pretty, too. She went above and beyond and even styled her.

In addition to the wonderful service, the store was beautiful, well organized, and sparkling clean!

We both left feeling like princesses! Thank you, Cherae and Rebeka for the positive experience! <3</Text>

< user_name>
Mackenzie Fowler</user_name>
< user_id>
110776546650908724894< /user_id>
< Date>
1546198206296<//Date>
<Rating>2</Rating>< Text>
I wasn't incredibly impressed with my experience here. Earlier this year, I went in with a friend who is getting married and helped her pick out a dress -- she seemed really excited and happy when she walked out of there. So when I got engaged, I thought, "I'll go back and hopefully feel the same way!" Not so.

I'm not sure if it's the time of year or what, but they had hardly any dresses in my size, which the stylist said is pretty popular. It IS right after Christmas so I'll give DB the benefit of the doubt on that one. Still, pretty disappointing when you have a 90-minute appointment and there are like 6 things to try on.

Another thing is our stylist was 20 minutes late to help us and then was in a big rush at the end to wrap it up. When you advertise 90-minute appointments, make it 90 minutes.

She also really wasn't around that much. There was a lot of waiting around between dresses, just standing awkwardly in half-zipped monstrosities, while she brought new stuff to try on. Again, maybe this was part of not having a lot in my size and she was looking for more. But it was still pretty awkward and my friend ended up having to do a lot of the zipping/buttoning/tugging.

Another thing is she kept bringing me these HUGE DRESSES. I told her right off the bat that we were having an outdoor, relatively informal wedding. Boom -- ball gowns. Ball gowns after ball gowns. With enormous trains. I appreciated being able to try on some things I wouldn't normally through her suggestions and it was fun to try on the first big, poofy, princess dress. But overall, I did not feel listened to.

And finally, what really solidified the whole underwhelming experience was when we were talking about my wedding, which isn't for another year and a half. I was casually mentioning (again) how it would be outdoors and informal and that our guest list really wasn't that big. And she said, "Well, your guest list isn't that big NOW."

Nope. Do not stand here and tell me what sort of wedding I want. Not all of us want big, sparkly princess weddings with $80,000 budgets and 300 guests. I'm getting married on a budget, on a lakeshore in October, surrounded by 40 of my/my partner's closest friends and relatives. Then we're going to a local brewery for the reception. A ball gown's just not gonna cut it, but thanks anyway.

Maybe most of these issues stemmed from a lack of dresses in my size and I can absolutely work with that. It happens, especially right after Christmas. But the not-feeling-listened-to part? Nah. I won't be back here.< /Text>

When I first got there I was a little confused as to where to go: if I was supposed to follow the lady, etc. but that was a quick solve. We headed to the back where the clearance was and picked out dresses. Mariah quickly came over and put them by my door to try them on. She was very quick to ask how things were and if I needed help and also for bringing a variety of accessories like a belt and a veil that really added to the dress. When I found a dress that was too expensive on accident, she found me another that was cheaper, but similar and I absolutely loved it! I definitely went in thinking this place was a chain and that I wouldn't like it, but they have tons of selection (which was a huge perk) and the staff was bubbly and helpful. I would recommend to anyone going dress shopping.</review>

I made an appointment to try on wedding gowns with my maid of honor who was in town for a couple of days. We were promptly greeted at the front desk and was checked in. Our sales associate... Jina, came to greet us with a smile and she happily looked over the pictures that I had brought in with me that I printed off the David's Bridal website. I have to note that this was my first time here and we made our appointment on a Saturday morning, so it was already starting to fill up with other potential brides and their family and friends. So they didn't have all the looks that I was hoping to try on that day... but Jina was wonderful enough to pull a few other looks that I may be interested in. She really was nice, attentive and overall a great help.

I didn't purchase anything at this visit, but booked another appointment on a Monday with Jina and this time my MOH and my fiancee were in attendance... and once again... Jina was the best. She understood that I was trying to get a feel for what overall looked best on me and while I'm not ready to exactly say, Yes to the dress... (my wedding is in October 2017), she was more than helpful and understood that I was just in the beginning stage of this process. But I will be going back and asking for her each and every time.

So if you're looking for a great associate... ask for Jina at this location, she'll totally help you out.<//text>
